{"author":{"id":"01671ff9032e46364812e0318334f210ee83239f58dc81dc28f5ed24ec9fc21c"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1723595210,"nonce":"s8Htajm9oHlt+20BMOohPpThF9g=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOJl1IZM6IWF7_","github-url":"https://github.com/nikitabobko/AeroSpace/issues/402#issuecomment-2287492863"},"message":"Is there an event that would trigger anytime a workspace is manipulated? If not I would be nice. Also I apologize for minimal information. I update my space indicators in sketchybar dynamically. I have another script that fires which removes old workspaces with no windows in them and adds the number of windows in a given workspace to the focused workspace. So when I use a rule to automatically move a window, sketchybar doesn't indicate that the space now has a window in it. This is really a minor annoyance, but it would be nice. \n\n\nScript in question for posterity.  It's a hack job. \n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env zsh\nPLUGIN_DIR=\"$HOME/.config/sketchybar/plugins\"\n\nif [[ -z \"$1\" ]]; then \n    1=$(aerospace list-workspaces --focused)\nfi\n\n# If space doesn't exist\nif ! sketchybar --query space.\"$1\" \u0026\u003e /dev/null; then \n    \n    # Get Position\n    position=\"\"\n    for i in {1..9}; do \n        if sketchybar --query space.\"$i\" \u0026\u003e /dev/null; then \n            position=\"$i\"\n            continue\n        fi\n        break\n    done\n\n\n    # Create Space\n    sketchybar --add item space.$1 left             \\\n    --subscribe space.$1 aerospace_workspace_change \\\n    --set space.$1                                  \\\n    background.color=0xff{{ .dracula.hex.purple }}  \\\n    background.corner_radius=5                      \\\n    background.height=20                            \\\n    background.drawing=off                          \\\n    icon.drawing=off                                \\\n    label=$1                                        \\\n    label.padding_right=6                           \\\n    click_script=\"aerospace workspace $1\"           \\\n    script=\"$PLUGIN_DIR/aerospace.sh $1\"            \\\n    --move space.$1 before chevron                  \\\n    --move space.$1 after space.$position\n\n    bash -c \"$PLUGIN_DIR/aerospace.sh $1\"\nfi\n\n# Remove Empty Spaces\nrm_spaces=()\nfor i in {1..9}; do\n    matched=0\n    for j in $(aerospace list-workspaces --all); do \n        if [[ \"$j\" -eq \"$i\" ]]; then \n            matched=1\n            break\n        fi\n    done\n\n    if [[ \"$matched\" -eq 1 ]]; then \n        continue\n    fi\n    rm_spaces+=(\"$i\")\ndone\n\nfor space in $rm_spaces; do\n    sketchybar --remove space.$space\ndone\n```","files":null}]}